.TH "vmw_cmdbuf_space_pool" 9 "vmw_cmdbuf_space_pool" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_cmdbuf_space_pool \- Set up a command buffer header with command buffer space from the main pool.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_cmdbuf_space_pool
.BI "(struct vmw_cmdbuf_man *man "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_cmdbuf_header *header "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "bool interruptible "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "man" 12
The command buffer manager.
.IP "header" 12
Pointer to the header to set up.
.IP "size" 12
The requested size of the buffer space.
.IP "interruptible" 12
Whether to sleep interruptible while waiting for space.
